Some wedding dress codes are fairly straightforward, like cocktail or black tie. Others are decidedly less so — think “fancy ranch,” “California chic” or “garden attire.” After attending bridal showers, buying gifts and booking flights, the last thing a wedding guest wants to do is decipher a confounding description of the preferred attire for the big day. In the midst of all the sartorial confusion, at least there’s room for humor. We’ve rounded up 25 funny tweets about wedding dress codes.